rest_of_day_open: I hope it'll go well. This past week was incredibly good on the professional side - slower paced, and I felt very competent. Usually when there's a super good week, I feel like the universe will balance it out and give me a bad week in the near future. So I'm hopeful... but I'm also a little tentative about it too.
critical_positive: I thought what went well was that we focused on what we had in common (faith, Asian parents) and connecting/bonding over that. It was also good to ask questions and just hear one another's stories and backgrounds. I think Nicki was very nice and I wish all the best for her future.
critical_negative: I didn't like the audio cut out every now and then. I'm not sure if it was the connection on my end, her end or the interface that we used... but that made it a little hard to hear her and I missed some key words every now and then.

rest_of_day_open: The rest of my week will probably be the same as my last week. I have no problem with that as my weeks have actually been pretty good, despite not having a job. critical_positive: I think both he and I did our best to listen to what the other person was saying so that there was a way to come back to topics to relate to it. We did our best to ask each other questions based on what we listened to. We also used anything we related to in the conversation to advance the conversation as well.

I suppose that I felt bad that he was asking me a lot of follow-up questions right away because that meant I would take up more time talking, and I wanted to ask him more questions as well to show that I cared about him too.
